<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="wild-adj">wild <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /waɪld/    美 /waɪld/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>野 (生) 的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>wild animals / flowers</strong> 
野生动物/野花</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>荒芜的；荒凉的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The island is a wild and lonely place. 
该岛荒无人烟。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He is abandoned in a wild area and has to find his way out.
他被丢在野外，必须找到出路。</p><footer>2015 北京改</footer></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>（行为）无法无天的；放荡的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The boy is wild and completely out of control. 
这个男孩很野，完全没法管教。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>（感情）强烈的；疯狂的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>His rock music makes the audience <strong>go wild</strong>. 
他的摇滚乐使听众疯狂。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>wildly /'waɪldli/ adv   </p></div>